Zheng said he had not seen his wife and children for nearly 30 days. For the first time in 13 years as property manager.

His 51 days of uninterrupted hard work were also rare in his career.

On New Year's Eve, he would check on security in his neighborhood, then go home and have dinner with his family to watch the gala.

But in the Spring Festival of, the practice was abandoned by a new outbreak.

On the eve of the city closure in Wuhan on January 22, Zheng Zongbao's family returned to their hometown in Jingzhou for the Lunar New Year. "Even if my family chose to stay in Wuhan, I would not dare to go home after work, " he said, speaking from his workplace just across the wall from the South China Seafood Market, where the outbreak first occurred.

Zheng Zongbao is the regional manager of Wuhan Vanke property in Hankou, the real estate company in the region of 6 properties in general responsible person. Among them, his administration of Vanke Hankow Legend, Tang Yue, Yuet Ting three sub-district, adjacent to the south China Seafood Market, Wuhan was classified as the epidemic level control area.

In fact, before the outbreak, the South China Seafood City supermarket danger, in the eyes of the community owners are everywhere.

Li Chong, owner of Yuet Ting, said, "The south China Seafood Market is full of rancid smells, rotten vegetables and leaves are everywhere, sewage is everywhere and shoes turn black when you step on them. The owners have complained many times and asked the competent authorities to move the market, but nothing has been done. "

In late December 2019, when a "virus of unknown origin" was discovered in the south China seafood market, Zheng became more vigilant, "because many of the residents in the community are tenants of the south China Seafood Market, and there are also apartments for sharing such as free and egg shells, " according to the information, one of the first new cases of coronary pneumonia was rented here.

Here is the "core zone" of the epidemic, the community is "the core of the CBD, " Li Chong described the situation at that time. He was glad that the outbreak did not become widespread in the community in later years.

Unlike Li, Zheng's vigilance against the virus stems from his memory and experience fighting SARS 17 years ago. At the time, Zheng Zongbao was a soldier serving in Qingdao, Shandong Province. "Our troops were on duty at Daokou in order to support the local fight against the epidemic. "

On December 31,2019, "We expected the worst, so we reported back to the group, urgently procured 84 disinfectants, dust masks and disposable medical masks, and started disinfection in public areas and popularizing prevention and control measures, " Zheng said.

The day after supplies arrived, the south China Seafood Market, which spans two blocks, was closed.

But few of the owners were alarmed, and very few went outside to put on face masks, Zheng recalled. It wasn't until Jan. 15, when news of the infection spread among the owners, that neighbors at the south China seafood market began to feel the danger.

Since then, property owners have called to ask about the epidemic situation, including "whether there are confirmed cases in the community? Is the epidemic serious? " In the face of these problems, Zheng Zongbao admitted that he has very limited information. But he believes that has lasted half a month of prevention and control measures for the owners to buy time.

The owner's nervousness soon spread to the staff of the property, "A young girl from the 1990s who was working as a receptionist in a community near the south China seafood market was getting three video calls a day from her family for fear of infection. The worry of the family made the little girl cry several times,"Zheng said, "As a property industry, our services can not be interrupted. While strengthening staff protection measures, we do our best to ensure that projects are not halted. "

On January 23rd and 26th, Wuhan announced that it was closing access to and from the city, and banning motor vehicles from the main urban areas. Tensions in the community are at their peak.

At that time, the property "housekeeper" Yang Jie's mobile phone every day is in the "beat" state. He needs to carry three cell phones a day to answer the owner's inquiries, including the outbreak of the community, as well as epidemic prevention and control measures. He admits he has limited information when it comes to explaining to property owners.

February 3, Zheng Zongbao through the circle of friends, learned that a community owner was diagnosed. On the same day, he also received a list of confirmed cases from the community, and according to community requirements, will be confirmed and suspected cases of building information to the owners, the community to adopt closed management measures.

In addition, the property also began to upgrade the intensity of killing: The community public areas for two comprehensive killing, the residential corridor on each floor of the cover-type killing; in the community set up a waste mask special trash can called on the owners to correctly discard waste masks, reducing the risk of virus transmission.

Li Chong recalled, "at that time, I once thought that the professional disinfection team sprayed disinfection water, smell is good, can bring a sense of security. "

The closure of the city stretched Zheng's available manpower to the limit. He had to carry a spray bottle filled with disinfectant on his back and put on a protective suit to sterilize the whole area. "disinfecting a residential area once takes half a day and twice a day, which is the most heavy work the property can do, " he said.

In order to solve the problem of eating, Zheng Zongbao also rode a tricycle in early February, found three gas companies towed back 10 bottles of liquefied gas, to ensure the normal operation of the staff canteen.

"through the co-ordination of the company, the community has also found a vegetable supplier. The vegetable bags, including one cabbage, two turnips and four potatoes, have been continuously supplied, " Zheng said, "order through a small procedure, and then the owners go downstairs in batches to get the food. Today's residential area, because the total closed appears quiet, the residents who need out of the community have been familiar with the temperature gun, protective clothing, also does not reject the pungent odor of disinfection water.

Tang Yue, a resident of the neighborhood, told reporters that he had adapted to the pace of life. Li Chong began to look forward to the end of the epidemic after the celebration, to the epidemic past, really want to go out to eat a meal, and then a good rest day.
